♫[ Hi-Fi Bass Sound]:Powerful 57mm stereo driver and advanced bluetooth 4.2 chip that aim to deliver you superior sound quality with high fidelity deep bass and crystal clear treble, lose yourself in immersive music even in the lowest volume levels!

♫[Super Features]: Wireless and wired flexible headphones,if the battery is low, you can switch to wired mode and enjoy music with a 3.5mm audio cable . Use FM radio and support SD card playback. You can listen to the FM radio using your headphones, or you can put the SD card on the SD card on your headphones to listen to music.Built-in Microphone and Control,over ear headphones provide high-quality built-in microphone for hands-free calls.

♫[Foldable Design]:The foldable Headband is not only designed for saving your desk space. Depending on your head/ear size/shape, it maybe feels like"on ear"for someone to wear which is designed to avoid sound leakage. In case of that and to get both audio and wearing comfort, please take off the headphone every 1-2 hrs to get your ears relax and protect them from muggy environment in use.

♫[Comfortable & Super Light]: These over ear Bluetooth headphones come with super soft pads and adjustable headband providing lasting comfort. GREAT COMFORT FOR ALL AGES. Ear cushion simulate human skin texture, ensuring lasting comfort.The Slider and softly padded headband allows you to find a perfect fit for different size of heads. Best wireless headphone for long term wearing.

♫[Quality service] :We check products at every level before out of storage. If you encounter any problems, please contact us in time, because we focus on providing each customer good guarantee of rights.
I got these for working out and they are great! I’ve had them for about two months and use them 5-6 times a week. The battery lasts forever, I usually only charge once every one to two weeks.

This headphone is wonderful.  I have tried several earbuds, headbands with speaker inserts, and over ear with disappointing sound quality and volume control or difficulty using.  Not so with this product.  The sound quality is fantastic and I have no problem controlling and adjusting volume!  I am able to connect easily with a windows laptop, chrome book laptop, IPAD, and several different android tablets.The written instructions come in a number of different languages, type fits are a bit small for my tired ancient  eyes, but fortunately, operation is extremely simple.
Too small, did not hold charge.

I returned to them. For one thing the battery was not lasting more than a couple hours after I charge them and it wasn't even able to couple them to any of my devices. So I charged it up overnight, try to couple it, go a way for a bit, come back in two hours, and no charge. Also they really are for people with very small ears

I wanted these to listen to music while cutting grass with a riding and walk-behind mower.The ear cups MAY be ok for children (dint have any to test this on), but for adult sized ears they are way too small - as such, they do very little to cancel any nose.  Also, because they are so small, they tend to not be very comfortable to use for extended periods.The sound quality is OK, I guess, nothing special here.  What they do, they do OK, also they were fairly easy to pair (wouldn't pair with my S10+ the 1st time around, paired well with Tab 6, then paired easily with S10+ the 2nd time)I will be keeping them, but will be looking for a better pair for mowing
The media could not be loaded.
The sound is good and the quality is good for the price. I will definitely buy again.
Bought for my 11 year old son for remote learning back in August. He says they're comfortable, battery lasts well and they also have a wire in case you forget to charge them. Good price too.

This is the second pair of headphones that we’ve purchased and I am returning them again. The fact that I now have to get my car and waste gas for a second time to return $15 headphones that I purchased for my four-year-old grandson is very sad. The problem is you do not wanna spend a lot of money for a four-year-old child however I can’t blame the child this time for any defective condition because it’s not even 30 days that we have the second pair of headphones. Do not waste your time even looking. I’m sure that there are plenty of headphones on Amazon around that price point that are much better quality
not bad and folding is good for travel

I like that they fold and can get small for travel. These are NOT over the ear cups. I got about half my ear into it and the rest is on top so for long listening it may hurt the ears.  But not horrible.  Sound was good! surprisingly so.  not audiophile of course but decent.  and a big step up from listening on notebook speakers.  the built in mic I have yet to try and havent tried noise canceling which there doesn't appear to be a switch for so another negative.  I think the better ones are 60 bucks and dont fold . so for some basics for travel these are good. I have a even tinier super light headphone thats bluetooth but not noise canceling for airplanes so my dec for these was def for airlines. I will report back after i fly.Loudness - these get VERY LOUD!  Bass - These have excellent BASS  Vocals - decent to good not audiophile. Listened to bowie ashes to ashes on amazon music and was quite balanced.  Headphone sizing - bands CLICK to positions. very good.  Plugging in the USB-B charger mini jack - a huge pain.  Has a micro SD slot.  I think they would benefit from a audio graphic equalizer to rebalance.
just what I was looking for

I love my gym. I really, really do. But the owner BLASTS music that is...ummm...not so great for lifting. I mean, Elvis? He keeps the volume up loud enough that even with my in-ear headphones on so loud it physically hurt, I could still hear the gym music over my own. So then it was like, my music clashing with "American Pie," which basically meant a headache every single day. So I wanted to get some (inexpensive) noise-canceling headphones to see if I could solve the problem, and these did the trick. I now listen to my own music (and ONLY my own!) at a reasonable volume. The fact that they fold for easier storage in my gym bag is a bonus.
Yeah so what that they are cheaply priced but they are worth it for kids and zoom meetings.

Now for being cheap no name brand it works perfectly for the kids during zoom meetings for school. It has blue tooth and headphone jack so when the battery is low they can still use the provided wire to hear the meeting. Now I will say this. The microphone works plugged in to the head jack or Bluetooth but for it picking up the kids voice it has a hard time if they are talking in a low voice. They almost have to speak up for the microphone to hear them talking or it kinda cuts in  and out. But for the price and quality and because I’m tired of loaning my kids my Bose and Powerbeats pro headphones for the meetings they work perfectly for what they need. Would definitely buy these again. For small ears the padding goes over their ears. It won’t go over mine as I’m an adult with adult sized ears ???? lol. But the kids really like them. I have them in red black. Blue black. And rose gold and white.
